# IDE Build Workflow (Mandatory — Do Not Regress)

**Status:** Verified working on Windows (2026-06). Strengthened 2026-07 after CMake Tools + vcpkg lock caused 10–30 min waits. F5 path verified 2026-07-10 (v0.8.82): **Build and Run task only — never CodeLLDB**.

Daily build/run **must** use tracked `.vscode/` + scripts — **not** CMake Tools configure/build/launch, **not** debugger attach on F5.

## Canonical dev path

| Action | How |
|--------|-----|
| **Build** | **Ctrl+Shift+B**, repo-root `빌드.bat`, or `.\scripts\build-release.ps1` |
| **Run (F5)** | Task **`Build and Run PIPBONG (Release)`** → `scripts/build-and-run.ps1` (`Start-Process`, **no debugger**) |
| **F5 success** | Terminal prints **`Started PIPBONG.exe`** right after build |
| **Output** | `build/Release/PIPBONG.exe` (cwd `build/Release/`) |
| **First configure** | `build-release.ps1` runs `cmake --preset default` **only** when `build/CMakeCache.txt` is missing |
| **Qt DLLs** | `.\scripts\deploy-qt.ps1` once when runtime DLLs missing — not every incremental link |
| **Recovery** | `.\scripts\recover-ide-build.ps1` then **Developer: Reload Window** |

## Required git-tracked files

These files **must** stay in the repo (`.gitignore` whitelists them). **Do not** delete, replace with CMake Tools defaults, or leave `.vscode/` fully gitignored.

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `.vscode/tasks.json` | **`Build Release`** (default build); **`Build and Run PIPBONG (Release)`** (default **test** = F5) |
| `.vscode/launch.json` | **`configurations: []`** — empty; F5 must not attach CodeLLDB |
| `.vscode/settings.json` | CMake Tools fully off + `pipbong.f5BuildAndRun: true` + `debug.openDebug: neverOpen` |
| `.vscode/extensions.json` | Recommendations / unwanted list — do not make CodeLLDB the F5 driver |

## `.vscode/settings.json` (required keys)

```json
{
    "dotnet.defaultSolution": "disable",
    "dotnet.autoDetect": "off",
    "cmake.enabled": false,
    "cmake.configureOnOpen": false,
    "cmake.configureOnEdit": false,
    "cmake.configureWhileEditing": false,
    "cmake.automaticReconfigure": false,
    "cmake.ignoreCMakeListsChanged": true,
    "cmake.useCMakePresets": "never",
    "cmake.buildBeforeRun": false,
    "cmake.ctest.enabled": false,
    "cmake.showConfigureWithDebuggerNotification": false,
    "cmake.options.statusBarVisibility": "hidden",
    "files.exclude": { "**/build-clangd": true },
    "debug.openDebug": "neverOpen",
    "debug.internalConsoleOptions": "neverOpen",
    "pipbong.f5BuildAndRun": true
}
```

## F5 / tasks / launch invariants

See also always-applied **`.cursor/rules/f5-build-and-run.mdc`**.

- Default build task: **`Build Release`** → `scripts/build-release.ps1`.
- Default test task: **`Build and Run PIPBONG (Release)`** → `scripts/build-and-run.ps1`.
- Daily F5: **unconditional** user keybinding → `workbench.action.tasks.test`. **Never** gate primary F5 on `workspaceFolder =~ /Sbm1\.0/i` (fails in Cursor → CodeLLDB hang).
- `launch.json` must stay **empty** `configurations`.
- Apply/repair keybindings: `.\scripts\fix-pipbong-cursor-f5.ps1` then **Reload Window**.
- **Never** use launch `type: "cmake"` or `preLaunchTask: "CMake: build …"`.
- **Never** restore CodeLLDB / `lldb` launch as the daily F5 path.

## Anti-patterns (known failures — do not reintroduce)

| Symptom | Cause |
|---------|--------|
| F5 starts **vcpkg install** / qtbase build (10–30 min) | CMake Tools **configure** on open/F5; `cmake.configureOnOpen` / `type: "cmake"` launch |
| **`vcpkg-running.lock` waiting…** in output | Parallel CMake Tools configure + `cmake --build`; stale lock |
| **"A CMake task is already running"** / build exit **-1** | Parallel CMake Tools tasks; status-bar **[Build]** / **[Configure]** clicked while another runs |
| **549+ Problems** / bogus IntelliSense | Separate **`build-clangd/`** tree — keep excluded; use **`build/`** only |
| Build OK → blank terminal / CodeLLDB / “Debug PIPBONG” tab → slow window | F5 = **Debug: Start Debugging**; or F5 `when` clause failed — run `fix-pipbong-cursor-f5.ps1` + Reload Window |
| `dist` exe fast but F5 slow | Same — debugger attach, not app startup |
| Slow every link | Re-enabling per-link `windeployqt` — dev preset uses `PIPBONG_SKIP_WINDEPLOY=ON` |
| AI runs `cmake --preset` every task | Full reconfigure + vcpkg manifest pass — use incremental `build-release.ps1` only |

## Recovery procedure (when IDE build / F5 breaks)

1. `.\scripts\recover-ide-build.ps1` (kills stuck cmake/vcpkg/msbuild, clears stale lock, restores `.vscode/` from git, runs `fix-pipbong-cursor-f5.ps1`).
2. **Developer: Reload Window** in Cursor.
3. Confirm **`cmake.enabled`: `false`**, `pipbong.f5BuildAndRun: true`, empty `launch.json` configurations.
4. **Do not** click CMake status-bar **[Configure]** — run `.\scripts\build-release.ps1` or Ctrl+Shift+B.
5. Verify: incremental build ~3–15 s; F5 prints **`Started PIPBONG.exe`** with no blank wait.
6. If DLL missing at runtime: `.\scripts\deploy-qt.ps1` once.

Manual equivalent: `git checkout -- .vscode/` + `.\scripts\fix-pipbong-cursor-f5.ps1` + kill cmake/vcpkg + reload window.

## AI / agent rules

- **Do not** “fix” IDE issues by re-enabling CMake Tools configure-on-open or adding `CMake: *` launch configs.
- **Do not** “fix” F5 by adding CodeLLDB / `Debug PIPBONG` back into `launch.json`.
- **Do not** remove `.vscode` from git tracking or overwrite `tasks.json` with CMake-generated build tasks.
- **Do not** run `cmake --preset default` when `build/CMakeCache.txt` exists — see `.cursor/rules/no-full-rebuild.mdc`.
- When user reports CMake Tools popups, vcpkg lock, 10–30 min builds, or blank F5 terminal: run recovery / `fix-pipbong-cursor-f5.ps1` first.

